    <!-- Application Structure Plan:
         1. Intro & Diagnosis: Explains the "100% Commits" graph using an interactive chart to contrast "Solo Dev" vs "Team Player".
         2. The Professional Workflow: A linear, interactive timeline. User clicks a step (Branch, Commit, PR, etc.) to see the "Why", "How" (Theory), and "Code" (Commands).
         3. Concept Explorer: Cards explaining Issues, PRs, and Code Review in depth.
         4. Cheat Sheet Dashboard: A filterable list of commands from the generated cheat sheet for quick reference.
    -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         1. Radar Chart (Chart.js): To visualize the user's current status (All commits) vs the Goal (Balanced skills). Justification: Directly addresses the user's uploaded image and initial query.
         2. Interactive Tabs/Timeline: To break down the Git flow into digestible steps. Justification: Git is a process, not just a list of commands.
         3. "Terminal" UI Component: To present code snippets contextually. Justification: Familiar environment for devs.
         4. NO SVG/Mermaid: All icons and diagrams built with CSS/HTML or Unicode.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
